-- Phase 1
((select id from public.phases where phase_number = 1),
  '01',
  'Mindset Data Analyst + Business Process Understanding',
  'Data Analyst Mindset + Business Process Understanding',
  'Unit 1: Pengumpulan & Persiapan Data',
  'Paham peran analyst di organisasi, alur kerja data (dari sumber ke insight), jenis data, dan cara identifikasi pertanyaan bisnis yang tepat.',
  'Understand the analyst''s role in an organization, data workflow (source to insight), data types, and how to identify the right business questions.',
  1, 90,
  E'## What is a Data Analyst?\n\nA **Data Analyst** bridges the gap between raw data and business decisions. Your job is to collect, clean, analyze, and communicate data insights to stakeholders who use them to make decisions.\n\n### The Data Workflow\n\n```\nBusiness Question → Data Collection → Cleaning → Analysis → Visualization → Insight\n```\n\n### Types of Data\n\n| Type | Description | Example |\n|------|-------------|----------|\n| **Structured** | Rows & columns, database-ready | Sales table, Excel sheet |\n| **Semi-structured** | Has some organization | JSON, XML, emails |\n| **Unstructured** | No fixed format | Images, videos, free text |\n\n### Quantitative vs Qualitative\n- **Quantitative**: Numbers you can measure (revenue, age, count)\n- **Qualitative**: Descriptive categories (gender, product type, region)\n\n### Asking the Right Business Question\n\nA good analyst starts by asking:\n1. **What decision** needs to be made?\n2. **What data** do we have to support it?\n3. **What''s the time frame**?\n4. **Who is the audience** for this insight?\n\n> **Example**: Instead of "analyze our sales data", ask "Why did Q3 revenue drop 15% compared to Q2, and which product categories contributed most?"\n\n### Your Role in the Organization\n\n- Work closely with business teams (marketing, ops, finance)\n- Translate business problems into data questions\n- Present findings clearly — no jargon\n- Recommend actionable next steps',
  E'## Apa itu Data Analyst?\n\nSeorang **Data Analyst** menjembatani kesenjangan antara data mentah dan keputusan bisnis. Tugasmu adalah mengumpulkan, membersihkan, menganalisis, dan mengkomunikasikan insight data kepada stakeholder yang menggunakannya untuk membuat keputusan.\n\n### Alur Kerja Data\n\n```\nPertanyaan Bisnis → Pengumpulan Data → Pembersihan → Analisis → Visualisasi → Insight\n```\n\n### Jenis-jenis Data\n\n| Tipe | Deskripsi | Contoh |\n|------|-----------|--------|\n| **Terstruktur** | Baris & kolom, siap database | Tabel penjualan, Excel |\n| **Semi-terstruktur** | Ada beberapa organisasi | JSON, XML, email |\n| **Tidak terstruktur** | Tidak ada format tetap | Gambar, video, teks bebas |\n\n### Kuantitatif vs Kualitatif\n- **Kuantitatif**: Angka yang bisa diukur (pendapatan, usia, jumlah)\n- **Kualitatif**: Kategori deskriptif (jenis kelamin, tipe produk, wilayah)\n\n### Mengajukan Pertanyaan Bisnis yang Tepat\n\n1. **Keputusan apa** yang perlu dibuat?\n2. **Data apa** yang kita miliki untuk mendukungnya?\n3. **Apa kerangka waktunya**?\n4. **Siapa audiensnya**?\n\n> **Contoh**: Daripada "analisis data penjualan kita", tanyakan "Mengapa pendapatan Q3 turun 15% dibanding Q2, dan kategori produk mana yang paling berkontribusi?"'),

((select id from public.phases where phase_number = 1),
  '02',
  'Excel untuk Analisis Data — Dasar hingga Menengah',
  'Excel for Data Analysis — Basic to Intermediate',
  'Unit 1 & 2: Persiapan & Validasi Data',
  'Pivot Table, VLOOKUP/XLOOKUP, INDEX-MATCH, conditional formatting, data validation, handling missing data di Excel.',
  'Pivot Tables, VLOOKUP/XLOOKUP, INDEX-MATCH, conditional formatting, data validation, handling missing data in Excel.',
  2, 90,
  E'## Excel for Data Analysis\n\nExcel remains the most widely used tool for data analysis in business. Mastering it is essential before moving to SQL or Python.\n\n### Pivot Tables\n\nPivot Tables let you summarize large datasets in seconds.\n\n**How to create:**\n1. Select your data range\n2. Insert → PivotTable\n3. Drag fields to Rows, Columns, Values\n\n```\nExample: Sales data with columns: Date, Region, Product, Revenue\n→ Pivot: Rows=Region, Values=SUM(Revenue)\n→ Result: Revenue by region at a glance\n```\n\n### VLOOKUP vs XLOOKUP\n\n```excel\n-- VLOOKUP (older, limited)\n=VLOOKUP(lookup_value, table_array, col_index, FALSE)\n\n-- XLOOKUP (modern, flexible)\n=XLOOKUP(lookup_value, lookup_array, return_array, "Not Found")\n```\n\nXLOOKUP advantages:\n- Can look left AND right\n- Returns multiple columns\n- Better error handling\n\n### INDEX-MATCH\n\nMore powerful than VLOOKUP for complex lookups:\n\n```excel\n=INDEX(return_range, MATCH(lookup_value, lookup_range, 0))\n```\n\n### Conditional Formatting\n\nHighlight data patterns visually:\n- **Color scales**: Heat map of values\n- **Data bars**: Bar chart inside cells\n- **Icon sets**: Traffic lights for KPI status\n\n### Data Validation\n\nPrevent bad data entry:\n- Dropdown lists for consistent categories\n- Number ranges (e.g., age must be 1–120)\n- Custom formulas\n\n### Handling Missing Data\n\n```excel\n-- Check if cell is empty\n=IF(ISBLANK(A2), "Missing", A2)\n\n-- Fill with average\n=IF(ISBLANK(A2), AVERAGE($A$2:$A$100), A2)\n\n-- Count missing values\n=COUNTBLANK(A2:A100)\n```',
  E'## Excel untuk Analisis Data\n\nExcel tetap menjadi alat yang paling banyak digunakan untuk analisis data dalam bisnis. Menguasainya sangat penting sebelum beralih ke SQL atau Python.\n\n### Pivot Table\n\nPivot Table memungkinkanmu meringkas dataset besar dalam hitungan detik.\n\n**Cara membuat:**\n1. Pilih rentang data\n2. Insert → PivotTable\n3. Seret field ke Rows, Columns, Values\n\n### VLOOKUP vs XLOOKUP\n\n```excel\n-- VLOOKUP (lama, terbatas)\n=VLOOKUP(nilai_pencarian, array_tabel, indeks_kolom, FALSE)\n\n-- XLOOKUP (modern, fleksibel)\n=XLOOKUP(nilai_pencarian, array_pencarian, array_kembalian, "Tidak Ditemukan")\n```\n\n### INDEX-MATCH\n\nLebih powerful dari VLOOKUP:\n\n```excel\n=INDEX(rentang_kembalian, MATCH(nilai_pencarian, rentang_pencarian, 0))\n```\n\n### Conditional Formatting\n\nSorot pola data secara visual:\n- **Color scales**: Heat map nilai\n- **Data bars**: Grafik batang di dalam sel\n- **Icon sets**: Lampu lalu lintas untuk status KPI\n\n### Menangani Data yang Hilang\n\n```excel\n-- Cek apakah sel kosong\n=IF(ISBLANK(A2), "Kosong", A2)\n\n-- Hitung nilai yang hilang\n=COUNTBLANK(A2:A100)\n```'),

((select id from public.phases where phase_number = 1),
  '03',
  'Data Cleaning di Excel + Statistik Dasar',
  'Data Cleaning in Excel + Basic Statistics',
  'Unit 2 & 3: Validasi Data & EDA',
  'Identifikasi dan perbaiki dirty data, duplikat, inkonsistensi; statistik deskriptif (mean, median, std dev), distribusi data, deteksi outlier.',
  'Identify and fix dirty data, duplicates, inconsistencies; descriptive statistics (mean, median, std dev), data distributions, outlier detection.',
  3, 90,
  E'## Data Cleaning in Excel\n\nReal-world data is messy. Up to 80% of an analyst''s time is spent cleaning data before any analysis.\n\n### Common Data Problems\n\n| Problem | How to Fix |\n|---------|------------|\n| Duplicates | Data → Remove Duplicates |\n| Extra spaces | =TRIM(A2) |\n| Inconsistent case | =PROPER(A2), =UPPER(A2), =LOWER(A2) |\n| Number stored as text | VALUE() or Text to Columns |\n| Inconsistent dates | Text to Columns → Date format |\n\n### Finding & Removing Duplicates\n\n```excel\n-- Highlight duplicates: Conditional Formatting → Duplicate Values\n-- Count duplicates:\n=COUNTIF($A$2:$A$100, A2) > 1\n\n-- Remove via: Data → Remove Duplicates\n```\n\n### Basic Statistics\n\n```excel\n=AVERAGE(range)    -- Mean\n=MEDIAN(range)     -- Median\n=STDEV(range)      -- Standard Deviation\n=MIN(range)        -- Minimum\n=MAX(range)        -- Maximum\n=PERCENTILE(range, 0.25)  -- 25th percentile (Q1)\n=PERCENTILE(range, 0.75)  -- 75th percentile (Q3)\n```\n\n### Understanding Distributions\n\n- **Normal**: Bell curve, mean ≈ median\n- **Right-skewed**: Long tail to the right, mean > median (e.g., income)\n- **Left-skewed**: Long tail to the left, mean < median\n\n### Detecting Outliers\n\n**IQR Method:**\n```\nQ1 = 25th percentile\nQ3 = 75th percentile\nIQR = Q3 - Q1\n\nOutlier if: value < Q1 - 1.5×IQR  OR  value > Q3 + 1.5×IQR\n```\n\n```excel\n-- Flag outliers in Excel\n=IF(OR(A2 < Q1 - 1.5*IQR, A2 > Q3 + 1.5*IQR), "Outlier", "Normal")\n```\n\n### Using Data Analysis ToolPak\n\nEnable in: File → Options → Add-ins → Analysis ToolPak\n- **Descriptive Statistics**: Full summary stats in one click\n- **Histogram**: Distribution visualization\n- **Correlation**: Relationship between variables',
  E'## Data Cleaning di Excel\n\nData dunia nyata itu berantakan. Hingga 80% waktu analyst dihabiskan untuk membersihkan data sebelum analisis apapun.\n\n### Masalah Data yang Umum\n\n| Masalah | Cara Memperbaiki |\n|---------|------------------|\n| Duplikat | Data → Remove Duplicates |\n| Spasi berlebih | =TRIM(A2) |\n| Huruf tidak konsisten | =PROPER(A2) |\n| Angka tersimpan sebagai teks | VALUE() |\n| Tanggal tidak konsisten | Text to Columns |\n\n### Statistik Dasar\n\n```excel\n=AVERAGE(rentang)   -- Rata-rata\n=MEDIAN(rentang)    -- Median\n=STDEV(rentang)     -- Standar Deviasi\n=MIN(rentang)       -- Minimum\n=MAX(rentang)       -- Maksimum\n```\n\n### Deteksi Outlier\n\n**Metode IQR:**\n```\nQ1 = persentil ke-25\nQ3 = persentil ke-75\nIQR = Q3 - Q1\n\nOutlier jika: nilai < Q1 - 1.5×IQR  ATAU  nilai > Q3 + 1.5×IQR\n```'),

-- Phase 2
((select id from public.phases where phase_number = 2),
  '04',
  'SQL Dasar — SELECT, Filter, Aggregasi',
  'Basic SQL — SELECT, Filter, Aggregation',
  'Unit 3 & 4: EDA & Penggunaan Tools',
  'SELECT, WHERE, ORDER BY, GROUP BY, HAVING, fungsi agregat (SUM/COUNT/AVG/MIN/MAX), analisis sederhana dari database nyata.',
  'SELECT, WHERE, ORDER BY, GROUP BY, HAVING, aggregate functions (SUM/COUNT/AVG/MIN/MAX), simple analysis from a real database.',
  4, 90,
  E'## Basic SQL\n\nSQL (Structured Query Language) is the universal language for working with databases. It''s the most in-demand skill for data analysts.\n\n### SELECT — Retrieve Data\n\n```sql\n-- Get all columns\nSELECT * FROM customers;\n\n-- Get specific columns\nSELECT first_name, last_name, email FROM customers;\n\n-- With alias\nSELECT first_name AS "First Name", revenue * 0.1 AS commission FROM orders;\n```\n\n### WHERE — Filter Rows\n\n```sql\n-- Comparison operators\nSELECT * FROM orders WHERE revenue > 1000;\nSELECT * FROM customers WHERE country = ''Indonesia'';\n\n-- Multiple conditions\nSELECT * FROM orders WHERE revenue > 1000 AND status = ''completed'';\nSELECT * FROM orders WHERE region = ''Jakarta'' OR region = ''Surabaya'';\n\n-- Pattern matching\nSELECT * FROM customers WHERE email LIKE ''%@gmail.com'';\n\n-- Range\nSELECT * FROM orders WHERE order_date BETWEEN ''2024-01-01'' AND ''2024-12-31'';\n\n-- List\nSELECT * FROM products WHERE category IN (''Electronics'', ''Clothing'', ''Food'');\n\n-- NULL check\nSELECT * FROM customers WHERE phone IS NOT NULL;\n```\n\n### ORDER BY — Sort Results\n\n```sql\nSELECT * FROM orders ORDER BY revenue DESC;  -- Highest first\nSELECT * FROM customers ORDER BY last_name ASC, first_name ASC;\n```\n\n### GROUP BY + Aggregate Functions\n\n```sql\n-- Total revenue by region\nSELECT region, SUM(revenue) AS total_revenue\nFROM orders\nGROUP BY region\nORDER BY total_revenue DESC;\n\n-- Count customers per country\nSELECT country, COUNT(*) AS customer_count\nFROM customers\nGROUP BY country;\n\n-- Average order value by product category\nSELECT category, \n       COUNT(*) AS orders,\n       AVG(revenue) AS avg_revenue,\n       MIN(revenue) AS min_rev,\n       MAX(revenue) AS max_rev\nFROM orders\nGROUP BY category;\n```\n\n### HAVING — Filter Groups\n\n```sql\n-- Only regions with total revenue > 50,000\nSELECT region, SUM(revenue) AS total\nFROM orders\nGROUP BY region\nHAVING SUM(revenue) > 50000;\n\n-- WHERE filters rows BEFORE grouping\n-- HAVING filters groups AFTER aggregation\n```\n\n### LIMIT\n\n```sql\n-- Top 10 orders by value\nSELECT * FROM orders\nORDER BY revenue DESC\nLIMIT 10;\n```',
  E'## SQL Dasar\n\nSQL (Structured Query Language) adalah bahasa universal untuk bekerja dengan database. Ini adalah skill yang paling banyak dicari untuk data analyst.\n\n### SELECT — Ambil Data\n\n```sql\n-- Semua kolom\nSELECT * FROM customers;\n\n-- Kolom tertentu\nSELECT first_name, last_name, email FROM customers;\n\n-- Dengan alias\nSELECT first_name AS "Nama Depan", revenue * 0.1 AS komisi FROM orders;\n```\n\n### WHERE — Filter Baris\n\n```sql\nSELECT * FROM orders WHERE revenue > 1000;\nSELECT * FROM customers WHERE country = ''Indonesia'';\n\n-- Beberapa kondisi\nSELECT * FROM orders WHERE revenue > 1000 AND status = ''completed'';\n\n-- Pencarian pola\nSELECT * FROM customers WHERE email LIKE ''%@gmail.com'';\n```\n\n### GROUP BY + Fungsi Agregat\n\n```sql\n-- Total pendapatan per wilayah\nSELECT region, SUM(revenue) AS total_pendapatan\nFROM orders\nGROUP BY region\nORDER BY total_pendapatan DESC;\n```'),

((select id from public.phases where phase_number = 2),
  '05',
  'SQL Lanjutan — JOIN, Subquery, CTE',
  'Advanced SQL — JOIN, Subquery, CTE',
  'Unit 3 & 4: EDA & Penggunaan Tools',
  'INNER/LEFT/RIGHT JOIN, subqueries, WITH clause (CTE), kombinasi multiple table untuk menjawab pertanyaan bisnis kompleks.',
  'INNER/LEFT/RIGHT JOIN, subqueries, WITH clause (CTE), combining multiple tables to answer complex business questions.',
  5, 90,
  E'## Advanced SQL: JOINs, Subqueries & CTEs\n\n### JOINs — Combining Tables\n\nReal databases have data spread across multiple tables. JOINs let you combine them.\n\n```sql\n-- INNER JOIN: Only matching rows from both tables\nSELECT o.order_id, c.first_name, o.revenue\nFROM orders o\nINNER JOIN customers c ON o.customer_id = c.id;\n\n-- LEFT JOIN: All rows from left table, matching from right (NULL if no match)\nSELECT c.first_name, COUNT(o.id) AS order_count\nFROM customers c\nLEFT JOIN orders o ON c.id = o.customer_id\nGROUP BY c.id, c.first_name;\n-- This includes customers with 0 orders!\n\n-- RIGHT JOIN: All rows from right table (less common, prefer LEFT JOIN)\nSELECT * FROM orders o\nRIGHT JOIN customers c ON o.customer_id = c.id;\n```\n\n**When to use which:**\n- `INNER JOIN`: You only want records that exist in BOTH tables\n- `LEFT JOIN`: You want ALL records from the first table, with optional matches\n\n### Subqueries\n\nA query inside another query:\n\n```sql\n-- Find customers who placed orders above average value\nSELECT first_name, last_name\nFROM customers\nWHERE id IN (\n  SELECT customer_id\n  FROM orders\n  WHERE revenue > (SELECT AVG(revenue) FROM orders)\n);\n\n-- Subquery in FROM clause\nSELECT region, avg_revenue\nFROM (\n  SELECT region, AVG(revenue) AS avg_revenue\n  FROM orders\n  GROUP BY region\n) AS regional_stats\nWHERE avg_revenue > 5000;\n```\n\n### CTEs (Common Table Expressions)\n\nCTEs make complex queries readable by naming intermediate results:\n\n```sql\nWITH high_value_orders AS (\n  SELECT customer_id, SUM(revenue) AS total\n  FROM orders\n  WHERE status = ''completed''\n  GROUP BY customer_id\n  HAVING SUM(revenue) > 10000\n),\ncustomer_details AS (\n  SELECT id, first_name, last_name, region\n  FROM customers\n)\nSELECT \n  cd.first_name,\n  cd.last_name,\n  cd.region,\n  hvo.total AS lifetime_value\nFROM high_value_orders hvo\nJOIN customer_details cd ON hvo.customer_id = cd.id\nORDER BY hvo.total DESC;\n```\n\n**CTEs vs Subqueries:**\n- CTEs are more readable and reusable within the same query\n- CTEs can reference themselves (recursive CTEs)\n- Use CTEs when logic is complex or repeated',
  E'## SQL Lanjutan: JOIN, Subquery & CTE\n\n### JOIN — Menggabungkan Tabel\n\n```sql\n-- INNER JOIN: Hanya baris yang cocok dari kedua tabel\nSELECT o.order_id, c.first_name, o.revenue\nFROM orders o\nINNER JOIN customers c ON o.customer_id = c.id;\n\n-- LEFT JOIN: Semua baris dari tabel kiri, cocok dari kanan\nSELECT c.first_name, COUNT(o.id) AS jumlah_order\nFROM customers c\nLEFT JOIN orders o ON c.id = o.customer_id\nGROUP BY c.id, c.first_name;\n```\n\n### CTE (Common Table Expression)\n\n```sql\nWITH order_tinggi AS (\n  SELECT customer_id, SUM(revenue) AS total\n  FROM orders\n  WHERE status = ''completed''\n  GROUP BY customer_id\n  HAVING SUM(revenue) > 10000\n)\nSELECT c.first_name, c.last_name, o.total\nFROM order_tinggi o\nJOIN customers c ON o.customer_id = c.id\nORDER BY o.total DESC;\n```'),

((select id from public.phases where phase_number = 2),
  '06',
  'SQL Window Functions + Analisis Kasus Bisnis',
  'SQL Window Functions + Business Case Analysis',
  'Unit 3 & 6: EDA & Interpretasi',
  'ROW_NUMBER(), RANK(), LAG()/LEAD(), NTILE() untuk analisis ranking, tren, dan perbandingan periode.',
  'ROW_NUMBER(), RANK(), LAG()/LEAD(), NTILE() for ranking, trend, and period comparison analysis.',
  6, 90,
  E'## SQL Window Functions\n\nWindow functions perform calculations across a set of rows related to the current row — without collapsing them into groups like GROUP BY does.\n\n### Syntax\n\n```sql\nfunction_name() OVER (\n  PARTITION BY column   -- optional: divide into groups\n  ORDER BY column       -- optional: define row order\n  ROWS/RANGE ...        -- optional: define window frame\n)\n```\n\n### ROW_NUMBER, RANK, DENSE_RANK\n\n```sql\n-- Rank customers by total spending\nSELECT \n  customer_id,\n  total_spent,\n  ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY total_spent DESC) AS row_num,\n  RANK()       OVER (ORDER BY total_spent DESC) AS rank,\n  DENSE_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY total_spent DESC) AS dense_rank\nFROM customer_totals;\n\n-- Difference: if two customers tie at rank 2:\n-- RANK gives them both 2, next gets 4\n-- DENSE_RANK gives them both 2, next gets 3\n-- ROW_NUMBER always gives unique numbers\n\n-- Top 3 products per category\nSELECT * FROM (\n  SELECT \n    category, product_name, revenue,\n    RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY revenue DESC) AS rnk\n  FROM products\n) ranked\nWHERE rnk <= 3;\n```\n\n### LAG and LEAD — Period Comparisons\n\n```sql\n-- Month-over-month revenue change\nSELECT \n  month,\n  revenue,\n  LAG(revenue, 1) OVER (ORDER BY month) AS prev_month_revenue,\n  revenue - LAG(revenue, 1) OVER (ORDER BY month) AS change,\n  ROUND(\n    (revenue - LAG(revenue, 1) OVER (ORDER BY month)) \n    / LAG(revenue, 1) OVER (ORDER BY month) * 100, 2\n  ) AS pct_change\nFROM monthly_sales;\n```\n\n### NTILE — Quartile / Percentile Buckets\n\n```sql\n-- Segment customers into 4 quartiles by spending\nSELECT \n  customer_id,\n  total_spent,\n  NTILE(4) OVER (ORDER BY total_spent) AS spending_quartile\nFROM customer_totals;\n-- Q1=lowest 25%, Q4=top 25% (high-value)\n```\n\n### SUM / AVG as Window Function\n\n```sql\n-- Running total\nSELECT \n  order_date,\n  revenue,\n  SUM(revenue) OVER (ORDER BY order_date) AS running_total\nFROM orders;\n\n-- Each row with its % of total\nSELECT \n  region,\n  revenue,\n  ROUND(revenue / SUM(revenue) OVER () * 100, 1) AS pct_of_total\nFROM orders;\n```',
  E'## SQL Window Functions\n\nWindow function melakukan perhitungan di sejumlah baris yang terkait dengan baris saat ini — tanpa menggabungkannya seperti GROUP BY.\n\n### ROW_NUMBER, RANK, DENSE_RANK\n\n```sql\n-- Ranking pelanggan berdasarkan total belanja\nSELECT \n  customer_id,\n  total_spent,\n  RANK() OVER (ORDER BY total_spent DESC) AS peringkat\nFROM customer_totals;\n\n-- Top 3 produk per kategori\nSELECT * FROM (\n  SELECT \n    category, product_name, revenue,\n    RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY category ORDER BY revenue DESC) AS rnk\n  FROM products\n) ranked\nWHERE rnk <= 3;\n```\n\n### LAG dan LEAD — Perbandingan Periode\n\n```sql\n-- Perubahan pendapatan bulan ke bulan\nSELECT \n  bulan,\n  pendapatan,\n  LAG(pendapatan, 1) OVER (ORDER BY bulan) AS pendapatan_bulan_lalu,\n  pendapatan - LAG(pendapatan, 1) OVER (ORDER BY bulan) AS perubahan\nFROM penjualan_bulanan;\n```'),

-- Phase 3
((select id from public.phases where phase_number = 3),
  '07',
  'Prinsip Visualisasi Data + Looker Studio',
  'Data Visualization Principles + Looker Studio',
  'Unit 5: Visualisasi & Penyajian Data',
  'Prinsip chart yang benar, warna & layout yang efektif, membangun dashboard di Looker Studio dari Google Sheets/BigQuery.',
  'Correct chart principles (when to use bar vs line vs pie), effective colors & layout, building dashboards in Looker Studio.',
  7, 90,
  E'## Data Visualization Principles\n\nGood visualization makes insights obvious. Bad visualization misleads or confuses.\n\n### Choosing the Right Chart\n\n| Goal | Best Chart |\n|------|------------|\n| Compare values | Bar chart |\n| Show trend over time | Line chart |\n| Show composition (parts of whole) | Pie / Donut (max 5 slices) |\n| Show distribution | Histogram, Box plot |\n| Show correlation | Scatter plot |\n| Show geographic data | Map chart |\n| Compare multiple categories over time | Stacked bar / Line |\n\n### The 5 Principles of Effective Visualization\n\n1. **Clarity**: One chart = one message\n2. **Context**: Always include titles, axis labels, units\n3. **Accuracy**: Start bar charts at zero; don''t truncate axes\n4. **Simplicity**: Remove chart junk (gridlines, 3D effects, shadows)\n5. **Color**: Use color purposefully, not decoratively\n\n### Color Best Practices\n\n- Use **sequential palettes** for ordered data (light → dark)\n- Use **diverging palettes** for data with a meaningful midpoint\n- Use **categorical palettes** for unrelated categories\n- Max 7 colors in one chart\n- Always consider colorblind-friendly palettes\n\n### Looker Studio Basics\n\n**Connect data sources:**\n- Google Sheets\n- BigQuery\n- CSV upload\n- 800+ connectors\n\n**Key components:**\n1. **Data source** — where your data lives\n2. **Charts** — visualizations (bar, line, table, scorecard)\n3. **Filters** — interactive controls\n4. **Date range** — time period selector\n\n**Dashboard best practices:**\n- Put the most important KPIs at the top\n- Use consistent colors throughout\n- Group related charts together\n- Add a date filter on every dashboard',
  E'## Prinsip Visualisasi Data\n\n### Memilih Chart yang Tepat\n\n| Tujuan | Chart Terbaik |\n|--------|---------------|\n| Bandingkan nilai | Bar chart |\n| Tampilkan tren waktu | Line chart |\n| Tampilkan komposisi | Pie/Donut (maks 5 irisan) |\n| Tampilkan distribusi | Histogram, Box plot |\n| Tampilkan korelasi | Scatter plot |\n\n### 5 Prinsip Visualisasi Efektif\n\n1. **Kejelasan**: Satu chart = satu pesan\n2. **Konteks**: Selalu sertakan judul, label sumbu, satuan\n3. **Akurasi**: Mulai bar chart dari nol\n4. **Kesederhanaan**: Hapus elemen tidak perlu\n5. **Warna**: Gunakan warna secara purposeful'),

((select id from public.phases where phase_number = 3),
  '08',
  'Power BI — Data Model, DAX, dan Dashboard Profesional',
  'Power BI — Data Model, DAX, and Professional Dashboard',
  'Unit 5 & 7: Visualisasi & Pelaporan',
  'Import data, data model & relationships, DAX basics (CALCULATE, SUMX, DATEADD), publish ke Power BI Service.',
  'Import data, data model & relationships, DAX basics (CALCULATE, SUMX, DATEADD), publish to Power BI Service.',
  8, 90,
  E'## Power BI for Data Analysts\n\nPower BI is Microsoft''s business intelligence tool — widely used in Indonesian enterprises.\n\n### Power BI Desktop Workflow\n\n```\n1. Get Data → 2. Transform (Power Query) → 3. Model → 4. Visualize → 5. Publish\n```\n\n### Importing & Transforming Data\n\n**Power Query** is your data cleaning layer:\n- Remove/rename columns\n- Filter rows\n- Split/merge columns\n- Change data types\n- Unpivot tables\n\n### Data Model & Relationships\n\nPower BI uses a star schema:\n- **Fact table**: Transactions, events (orders, sales)\n- **Dimension tables**: Context (customers, products, dates)\n\n```\n[Date Dim] ──┐\n[Customer Dim] ──┤── [Orders Fact] ──┤── [Product Dim]\n[Region Dim] ──┘\n```\n\n**Create relationships**: Model view → drag fields between tables\n\n### DAX Basics\n\nDAX (Data Analysis Expressions) is Power BI''s formula language:\n\n```dax\n-- Basic measures\nTotal Revenue = SUM(Orders[Revenue])\nOrder Count = COUNT(Orders[OrderID])\nAvg Order Value = AVERAGE(Orders[Revenue])\n\n-- CALCULATE: Change filter context\nRevenue Jakarta = CALCULATE(\n    SUM(Orders[Revenue]),\n    Customers[Region] = "Jakarta"\n)\n\n-- Year-over-year comparison\nRevenue LY = CALCULATE(\n    [Total Revenue],\n    DATEADD(''Date''[Date], -1, YEAR)\n)\n\nYoY Growth % = DIVIDE([Total Revenue] - [Revenue LY], [Revenue LY])\n```\n\n### Publishing to Power BI Service\n\n1. File → Publish → Select workspace\n2. Set refresh schedule (daily/hourly)\n3. Share dashboard link with stakeholders\n4. Set row-level security if needed',
  E'## Power BI untuk Data Analyst\n\n### Alur Kerja Power BI Desktop\n\n```\n1. Get Data → 2. Transform (Power Query) → 3. Model → 4. Visualisasi → 5. Publish\n```\n\n### DAX Dasar\n\n```dax\n-- Measure dasar\nTotal Pendapatan = SUM(Orders[Revenue])\nJumlah Order = COUNT(Orders[OrderID])\n\n-- CALCULATE: Ubah konteks filter\nPendapatan Jakarta = CALCULATE(\n    SUM(Orders[Revenue]),\n    Customers[Region] = "Jakarta"\n)\n\n-- Perbandingan tahun ke tahun\nPendapatan TL = CALCULATE(\n    [Total Pendapatan],\n    DATEADD(''Date''[Date], -1, YEAR)\n)\n```'),

((select id from public.phases where phase_number = 3),
  '09',
  'Data Storytelling & Pembuatan Laporan Analisis',
  'Data Storytelling & Analysis Report Writing',
  'Unit 6 & 7: Interpretasi & Pelaporan',
  'Struktur laporan analisis yang baik, cara narasi dari data ke rekomendasi, simulasi presentasi ke stakeholder.',
  'Structure of a good analysis report, narrative from data to recommendations, stakeholder presentation simulation.',
  9, 90,
  E'## Data Storytelling\n\nData without a story is just numbers. Great analysts know how to turn analysis into decisions.\n\n### The Story Arc for Data\n\n```\n1. SITUATION — What''s the context?\n2. COMPLICATION — What''s the problem or question?\n3. RESOLUTION — What does the data show?\n4. RECOMMENDATION — What should we do?\n```\n\n### Structure of an Analysis Report\n\n**1. Executive Summary** (1 paragraph)\n- Key finding in plain language\n- The most important recommendation\n\n**2. Background & Objective**\n- What business question are we answering?\n- Why does it matter?\n\n**3. Methodology**\n- Data sources used\n- Time period covered\n- Key assumptions\n- Limitations\n\n**4. Key Findings**\n- 3–5 main insights, each supported by a chart\n- Lead with the most impactful finding\n\n**5. Recommendations**\n- Specific, actionable steps\n- Prioritized by impact vs effort\n- Include expected outcomes\n\n**6. Appendix**\n- Detailed tables, raw data\n- Technical methodology notes\n\n### Presenting to Stakeholders\n\n**Know your audience:**\n- **CEO/CFO**: Big picture, financial impact, 5-minute summary\n- **Marketing team**: Channel performance, campaign ROI\n- **Operations**: Process efficiency, bottlenecks\n\n**The Pyramid Principle:**\n- Start with your conclusion (don''t bury it)\n- Then support it with evidence\n- Then provide detail if needed\n\n**Common mistakes:**\n- Showing every chart you made\n- Using technical jargon\n- Not having a clear recommendation\n- Ending with "Questions?"',
  E'## Data Storytelling\n\n### Arc Cerita untuk Data\n\n```\n1. SITUASI — Apa konteksnya?\n2. KOMPLIKASI — Apa masalah atau pertanyaannya?\n3. RESOLUSI — Apa yang ditunjukkan data?\n4. REKOMENDASI — Apa yang harus kita lakukan?\n```\n\n### Struktur Laporan Analisis\n\n**1. Ringkasan Eksekutif** (1 paragraf)\n**2. Latar Belakang & Tujuan**\n**3. Metodologi**\n**4. Temuan Utama** (3–5 insight)\n**5. Rekomendasi** (spesifik & actionable)\n**6. Lampiran**\n\n### Prinsip Piramida\n- Mulai dengan kesimpulanmu\n- Dukung dengan bukti\n- Berikan detail jika diperlukan'),

-- Phase 4
((select id from public.phases where phase_number = 4),
  '10',
  'Python untuk Data Analyst — Pandas, EDA, dan Automation',
  'Python for Data Analysts — Pandas, EDA, and Automation',
  'Unit 3 & 4: EDA & Penggunaan Tools',
  'Python setup (Google Colab), Pandas (read/filter/groupby/merge), Matplotlib & Seaborn untuk visualisasi, automation laporan Excel.',
  'Python setup (Google Colab), Pandas (read/filter/groupby/merge), Matplotlib & Seaborn for visualization, automating Excel reports.',
  10, 90,
  E'## Python for Data Analysts\n\nPython automates repetitive tasks and handles data too large for Excel.\n\n### Setup: Google Colab (No Installation)\n\nGo to [colab.research.google.com](https://colab.research.google.com) — free, cloud-based Python notebook.\n\n### Pandas Basics\n\n```python\nimport pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\n\n# Load data\ndf = pd.read_csv("sales_data.csv")\ndf = pd.read_excel("report.xlsx", sheet_name="Sheet1")\n\n# Explore\ndf.shape          # (rows, columns)\ndf.head(10)       # First 10 rows\ndf.info()         # Column types and nulls\ndf.describe()     # Summary statistics\ndf.isnull().sum() # Missing value count per column\n\n# Filter\nhigh_value = df[df["revenue"] > 1000]\njakarta = df[df["region"] == "Jakarta"]\ncombined = df[(df["revenue"] > 1000) & (df["status"] == "completed")]\n\n# Select columns\ndf[["customer_id", "revenue", "region"]]\n\n# New columns\ndf["commission"] = df["revenue"] * 0.1\ndf["month"] = pd.to_datetime(df["order_date"]).dt.month\n\n# Group By\ndf.groupby("region")["revenue"].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)\ndf.groupby("category").agg({"revenue": ["sum","mean","count"]})\n\n# Merge (like SQL JOIN)\nmerged = pd.merge(orders, customers, on="customer_id", how="left")\n```\n\n### Matplotlib & Seaborn\n\n```python\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport seaborn as sns\n\n# Bar chart\nregion_sales = df.groupby("region")["revenue"].sum()\nregion_sales.plot(kind="bar", color="steelblue")\nplt.title("Revenue by Region")\nplt.ylabel("Revenue (IDR)")\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()\n\n# Distribution\nsns.histplot(df["revenue"], bins=30, kde=True)\n\n# Correlation heatmap\nsns.heatmap(df.corr(), annot=True, cmap="coolwarm")\n```\n\n### Automating Excel Reports with openpyxl\n\n```python\nfrom openpyxl import Workbook\nfrom openpyxl.styles import Font, PatternFill\n\nwb = Workbook()\nws = wb.active\nws.title = "Sales Report"\n\n# Write header\nheaders = ["Region", "Revenue", "Orders"]\nfor col, header in enumerate(headers, 1):\n    ws.cell(row=1, column=col, value=header)\n\n# Write data\nfor row, (region, revenue, orders) in enumerate(data, 2):\n    ws.cell(row=row, column=1, value=region)\n    ws.cell(row=row, column=2, value=revenue)\n    ws.cell(row=row, column=3, value=orders)\n\nwb.save("monthly_report.xlsx")\n```',
  E'## Python untuk Data Analyst\n\n### Pandas Dasar\n\n```python\nimport pandas as pd\n\n# Muat data\ndf = pd.read_csv("data_penjualan.csv")\n\n# Eksplorasi\ndf.shape          # (baris, kolom)\ndf.head(10)       # 10 baris pertama\ndf.info()         # Tipe kolom dan null\ndf.describe()     # Statistik ringkasan\n\n# Filter\nnilai_tinggi = df[df["pendapatan"] > 1000]\n\n# Group By\ndf.groupby("wilayah")["pendapatan"].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)\n\n# Merge\nmerged = pd.merge(orders, customers, on="customer_id", how="left")\n```'),

((select id from public.phases where phase_number = 4),
  '11',
  'Project Final — End-to-End Data Analysis',
  'Final Project — End-to-End Data Analysis',
  'Unit 1–7: Semua unit terintegrasi',
  'Project portfolio lengkap: dari data collection, cleaning, SQL analysis, sampai dashboard final + laporan bisnis.',
  'Complete portfolio project: from data collection, cleaning (Python/Excel), SQL analysis, to final dashboard + business report with recommendations.',
  11, 180,
  E'## Final Project: End-to-End Data Analysis\n\nThis session brings together everything you''ve learned into a complete portfolio project.\n\n### Project Brief\n\n**Scenario**: You are a Data Analyst at a retail company. The Head of Business asks:\n\n> *"Our revenue has been flat for 6 months. I need to understand which customer segments, product categories, and regions are underperforming — and what we should do about it."*\n\n### Project Deliverables\n\n1. **Data Preparation** (Python/Excel)\n   - Load and clean the provided dataset\n   - Document data quality issues found\n   - Create a clean, analysis-ready dataset\n\n2. **SQL Analysis** (in the SQL Playground)\n   - Customer segmentation by lifetime value\n   - Product category performance\n   - Regional trends\n   - Month-over-month growth using window functions\n\n3. **Dashboard** (Power BI or Looker Studio)\n   - Executive KPI summary\n   - Customer segment breakdown\n   - Product performance by category\n   - Regional heatmap\n   - Trend over 12 months\n\n4. **Business Report** (Word/Google Docs)\n   - Executive summary (1 page)\n   - 5 key findings with supporting charts\n   - 3 prioritized recommendations\n   - Appendix with methodology\n\n### Evaluation Criteria\n\n| Criterion | Weight |\n|-----------|--------|\n| Data quality & cleaning | 20% |\n| SQL query correctness | 25% |\n| Dashboard clarity | 25% |\n| Business recommendations | 20% |\n| Presentation quality | 10% |\n\n### Tips for a Strong Portfolio Project\n\n- Tell a story — connect all pieces into one narrative\n- Use real business language, not technical jargon\n- Every recommendation should be specific and measurable\n- Show your methodology transparently',
  E'## Project Final: Analisis Data End-to-End\n\n### Brief Project\n\n**Skenario**: Kamu adalah Data Analyst di perusahaan retail. Kepala Bisnis bertanya:\n\n> *"Pendapatan kami stagnan selama 6 bulan. Saya perlu memahami segmen pelanggan, kategori produk, dan wilayah mana yang underperforming — dan apa yang harus kita lakukan."*\n\n### Deliverable Project\n\n1. **Persiapan Data** (Python/Excel)\n2. **Analisis SQL** (di SQL Playground)\n3. **Dashboard** (Power BI atau Looker Studio)\n4. **Laporan Bisnis** (Word/Google Docs)\n\n### Kriteria Evaluasi\n\n| Kriteria | Bobot |\n|----------|-------|\n| Kualitas & pembersihan data | 20% |\n| Kebenaran query SQL | 25% |\n| Kejelasan dashboard | 25% |\n| Rekomendasi bisnis | 20% |\n| Kualitas presentasi | 10% |\n'),

((select id from public.phases where phase_number = 4),
  '12',
  'Etika & Keamanan Data + Simulasi Uji Kompetensi BNSP',
  'Data Ethics & Security + BNSP Competency Simulation',
  'Unit 8: Keamanan & Etika Data',
  'UU PDP Indonesia, prinsip data privacy, etika penggunaan data. Simulasi lengkap uji kompetensi BNSP.',
  'Indonesian PDP Law, data privacy principles, data use ethics. Full BNSP competency exam simulation.',
  12, 90,
  E'## Data Ethics & Security\n\n### Indonesia''s Personal Data Protection Law (UU PDP)\n\nEffective since October 2024, UU PDP No. 27/2022 governs personal data in Indonesia:\n\n**Key definitions:**\n- **Personal data**: Any information that identifies an individual\n- **Sensitive data**: Health, biometrics, financial, criminal records, political views\n- **Data controller**: The entity that determines purpose of processing\n- **Data processor**: The entity that processes on behalf of the controller\n\n**Individual rights under UU PDP:**\n1. Right to know how data is used\n2. Right to access personal data\n3. Right to correct inaccurate data\n4. Right to delete data\n5. Right to withdraw consent\n6. Right to object to automated decisions\n\n**Obligations for organizations:**\n- Obtain explicit consent before processing\n- Implement appropriate security measures\n- Report data breaches within 14 days\n- Appoint a Data Protection Officer (for large-scale processing)\n- Penalties: up to IDR 2 billion or 2% of annual revenue\n\n### Data Ethics Principles\n\n1. **Transparency**: Be clear about how data is used\n2. **Purpose limitation**: Use data only for its stated purpose\n3. **Data minimization**: Collect only what''s needed\n4. **Accuracy**: Keep data correct and up-to-date\n5. **Security**: Protect data from unauthorized access\n6. **Accountability**: Take responsibility for data practices\n\n### BNSP Competency Framework\n\nThe BNSP (Badan Nasional Sertifikasi Profesi) certification for Data Analyst covers 8 units:\n\n| Unit | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| 1 | Data collection & preparation |\n| 2 | Data validation |\n| 3 | Exploratory data analysis |\n| 4 | Using analysis tools |\n| 5 | Data visualization & presentation |\n| 6 | Interpretation of analysis results |\n| 7 | Analysis reporting |\n| 8 | Data security & ethics |\n\n### Simulation: BNSP Assessment\n\n**Practical demonstration** — you will be asked to:\n- Import and clean a dataset\n- Write SQL queries to answer business questions\n- Build a dashboard in Power BI or Looker Studio\n- Present findings and recommendations\n\n**Written test** — covers:\n- Statistical concepts\n- SQL syntax and usage\n- Data visualization principles\n- Ethics and regulations\n\n**Assessor interview** — be prepared to:\n- Explain your analysis methodology\n- Justify your recommendations\n- Discuss how you handled data quality issues',
  E'## Etika & Keamanan Data\n\n### UU PDP Indonesia (No. 27/2022)\n\nBerlaku sejak Oktober 2024:\n\n**Hak individu:**\n1. Hak untuk mengetahui penggunaan data\n2. Hak akses data pribadi\n3. Hak mengoreksi data tidak akurat\n4. Hak menghapus data\n5. Hak menarik persetujuan\n\n**Sanksi**: Hingga IDR 2 miliar atau 2% dari pendapatan tahunan\n\n### Prinsip Etika Data\n\n1. **Transparansi**: Jelas tentang penggunaan data\n2. **Pembatasan tujuan**: Gunakan data hanya untuk tujuan yang dinyatakan\n3. **Minimisasi data**: Kumpulkan hanya yang diperlukan\n4. **Akurasi**: Jaga data tetap benar\n5. **Keamanan**: Lindungi dari akses tidak sah\n6. **Akuntabilitas**: Bertanggung jawab atas praktik data');
